Wracked by insomnia and wanderlust, Kou Yamori is driven onto the moonlit streets every night in an aimless search for something he can’t seem to name. His nightly ritual is marked by purposeless introspection — until he meets Nazuna, who might just be a vampire! Kou’s new companion could offer him dark gifts and a vampire’s immortality. But there are conditions that must be met before Kou can sink his teeth into vampirism, and he’ll have to discover just how far he’s willing to go to satisfy his desires before he can heed the Call of the Night!
(Source: Sentai Filmworks)
Comedy, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! MgRonald’s best demon lord worker is back, climbing the corporate ladder to become ruler of Earth. But Maou’s plans of domination might need to be put on hold when a small girl claims to be his and Emi’s child! (Source: Crunchyroll)
Akutou Ikka no Manamusume, Tenseisaki mo Otome Game no Gokudou Reijoudeshita.: Saijoukyuu Ranku no Akuyaku-sama, sono Dekiai wa Fuyoudesu! @COMIC

After her sudden death at the hands of an assassin, the former granddaughter of a yakuza boss reincarnates in an otome game as the heroine. The game is, of course, set in the time of early European mafia (but with magic), specifically a kingdom where the royal family is supported behind the scenes by five major gangsters!

A dangerous love game between a former yakuza heiress and her villain fiancé begins!

(Source: TO Books, translated)
Fukushuu Kansuisha no Jinsei Nishuume Isekaitan THE COMIC

Five years ago, in the middle of winter, Kosuke Kurono's beloved sister was raped and murdered. Ever since then, he has devoted his life to revenge. When he finally avenged his sister's death, Kurono had nothing left to live for, and he decided to end his own life, too. But instead, he was reincarnated into another world, and given the Black Magic wielded by the great heroes of the past. Being told that his sister might have reincarnated into this world, too, he set out to look for her!

(Source: Comic Ride, translated)
